Version 1.6.3
2023-04-08 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Got rid of update loop and just drawn when needed. This is much friendlier
over slow connections.

Version 1.5.4
2021-02-27 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Changed ACS_VLINE with the '|' character
* Backspace fix
* Removed debugging output

Version 1.5.3
2021-02-23 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Fixed run away server when client disconnects unexpectedly.

Version 1.5.2
2020-04-26 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Updated documentation.
* Improved asynchronous IO.
* Fixed domain socket management.
* Added reduced privileges.

Version 1.5.1
2020-04-26 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Fixed new messages being dropped when scroll buffer is full.
* Updated documentation about badly behaving bot that don't read their input.

Version 1.5
2020-04-17 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Made lchatd less verbose as user join and leave.
* Private messages are now sent with server commands.
* Lots of polishing of the chat client.
* Documents updated.

Version 1.4
2019-07-03 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Added bot command line option to the lchat client.
* Added message command line option to lchat client.
* Further performance improvements to lchat client.
* Many bug and race fixes.

Version 1.3.3
2019-06-30 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Dropped the CPU usage and improved responsiveness.

Version 1.3.2
2019-04-08 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Fixed FreeBSD wide character support.

Version 1.3.1
2019-04-03 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Fixed systemd services script to use user group for chat socket.
* Fixed FreeBSD build.

Version 1.3.0
2019-03-25 Ron Wills <ron@digitalcombine.ca>

* Enabled unicode if the terminal supports it.
* Improved message input editing.

